results.name: a(n) is number of nonnegative integers not exceeding n which have no decimal digits occurring in n and respectively prime to n.
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..9999
example: Let n=12. Numbers which are prime to 12 are 1,5,7,11. However, 1 and 11 are not acceptable by the condition. So, a(12)=2.
